title: I am (Two)
author: ibreez
text: i am a mad scientist on verge.  i wonder if i can set the world straight.  i hear the willow in the breeze.  i see myself solving the worldâ’s hunger problem.  i want to go across the world.  i am a mad scientist on verge.   i pretend to be happy,  when down in my soul i know the truth.  i feel my eyelids getting heavy.  i touch the world with my hand.  i worry about how bitter the truth is.  i cry about how i lie.  i am a mad scientist on verge.   i understand prejudices.  i say that women should have equal rights.  i dream of a dream so vivid,  it seems like a different world.  i try to keep my nose clean,  as hard as it seems.  i hope for good to prevail.  i am a mad scientist on verge.

title: Color

text: itâ’s a flash of brilliant color.  a hue so light,  it shocks the eye.  there are many different shades of this color in hair.  it flows shimmering,  sometimes it seems as though itâ’s white.  it pops up everywhere during spring,  a pest to all.   itâ’s been taunted on the head of man,  for its color.  what color,  you ask? why tow-headed blonde,  of course.

title: I Wish

title: I Am

title: Bluebell Wood
author: isla
text: deep in the heart of bluebell wood,  slender grey trees with elegant fronds.  amid a still ocean of purple dreams,  the perfumed bluebells reaching for the dying sun.  i sense you.   past fields of golden yellow stalks,  artificial in the hazy lilac of bluebell wood.  you tread reverently over the tops of the flowers,  brushing past a branch on your carpet of tranquility.  i hear you.   amongst a peaceful glade of delicate ferns,  in the twilit shadows of the setting sun.  the misty air is sweet with your joy,  admiring the beauty of the waving petals.  i smell you.   the sky is swathed with bands of color,  melancholy grey clouds and red rimmed bursts of orange.  below the heavens of unfathomable indigo,  the day ends with mournful longing for times past.  i feel you.   wrapped in a haze of subdued blue,  edged with the hope of sun after rain.  a stunning rainbow encases your cloudy bed,  i stare at your pearly white figure with a smile to banish a blizzard.  i see you.   we are so close,  yet universes apart,  trapped,  you in your skybound realm.  me,  in my beautiful bluebell wood,  sharing our hopes,  secrets and dreams.  i know you.   although separated by the fabric of star studded space.  your spirit lives on in my heavy heart.  here,  gazing into the panorama of the shifting heavens,  i'll wait for you to call me in my lonely bluebell wood.  i miss you. . .

title: Stepping up to the Plate

text: stepping up to the plate  grab your batting gloves,  helmet,  and bat,  and step up to the on deck circle,  take your practice swings and get your timing down,  stay cool â– the pitcher throws bullets,  step up to the plate; wipe the sweat off your face,  and get ready to go,  take a few more warm-up swings,   and now youâ’re in control,  youâ’re the king,  line your feet so theyâ’re straight,  your back leg is where youâ’ve gotta keep your weight,  fingers lined up on the bat,  eyes focused on the pitcher,  stay loose,  donâ’t be stiff,  stand on the balls of your feet,  bats not to high,  not to low,  elbows out,  just barely though.  now the pitcher winds up and is ready to throw.  itâ’s almost as everythingâ’s in slow mo,  then the release and were back to normal speed,  the ball comes speeding toward you,  take a small step and pull your bat back a tad,  swing  down into the ball and donâ’t uppercut,  last thing you want is a wimpy pop up,  keep your head on the ball the whole time,  twist you feet toward the pitcher,  and turn your hips quickly,  swing hard,  and donâ’t slow your arms down,  follow through strong,  perfect swing,  but hitting something round with something round isnâ’t easy,  pop! the ball makes hard contact with the catcherâ’s mitt,  strike one,  start everything over again.

title: What If He Never Met Her?

text: what if he never met her,  would he be my friend?  what if he never met her,   would he have ever started?  what if he never met her,   would he have gotten hurt?  what if he never met her,   would he be in trouble?  what if he never met her,   would he have different friends?  what if he never met her,   would he be as stupid as an ant?  what if he never met her,   would he be any smarter?  what if he never met her,   would he know what those things are?  what if he never met her,   would he be any nicer?  what if he never met her,   would he be so obscure?  what if he never met her,   would he tell people more?  what if he never met her,   would he like the same things?  what if he never met her,   would his parents be as mad?  if he never met her,   he'd still be my friend.

title: The Nazi's Darkness
author: jackson
text: i used to remember the suns great shine,   but now i only see the nazi's cold darkness,    i always thought i could see the world,  but i never thought i would be confined to this small frightening cage,    i once was able to be free and fine,   but now i am able only to be caged and beaten,   if i could i would break free from this place,  this time,  this darkness,   i would laugh at these people for their wrongs and theories,   i never would come back for the beating and deaths,   but i might want a glimpse so i might see why they have done so,   i can't honestly do anything in this cold,  black darkness  but i can believe that i may see the light  i won't give up hope for those fighting with me  but i might create more simply to keep us moving stronger  i used to know the nice,  warm light  but now i am confined in the horrid,  fearsome darkness.

title: Last Warning (Romeo & Juliet)

title: Life as a Vampire
author: jade
text: penetrating human life  creeping through the shadows tall and mysterious cloaked in black hiding as a vampire.   scared mortals. . .  see how they run? away from the darkest creature on earth.  away from the blood thirsty being,  waiting to pounce and rip out a human life.  this is what it's like to be a vampire.    the world passes by our kind our existence never ceasing.  only by the sun or fire shall our kind die forever.  the weaknesses of vampires.   we never age,  we never grow,  we stay like we were long ago.  like we were when we were made.  made into this monster.  the monster called the vampire.   our pale skin,  our lonely eyes.  we never see the day,  all we see is  night.   the starlit night,  with the light from the moon.   this is the life as a vampire.

text: i met a cat face to face the year when i was nine,  i took a tripe to outer state i braved a pinhead's den.   i wrestled with a wicked rat,  i fought a great white snake,  i trailed a cat down a hole,  i hunted for a snake.   i stowed aboard a subway,  i opened magic windows,  i traveled in a time clock and searched for cats and dogs.   i climbed atop a lizard's head,  i found a pot of mold,  i did all this in books i read when i was nine years old.

title: You and me.
author: janie
text: i can neither compare thee,   to the on going sway of the lilac tree.  nor can i compare thee,  to me.  you are nor the wind,  nor the land.  nor can i compare thee,  to the coarse sand,  so gently running through my hand.  i am the shadow,  you are the sun.  beams of light so golden,  you have the defiance,  and the reliance from me.  you are the absolution,  for which i have no solution.  you are nor the thunder,  the thunder i which i see.  the fire in your heart,  you dire confession,  for which i know,  i know that you've been waiting to self combust.  your losing that lust,  your losing your shine,  you are no longer mine.  your the sight of faded flowers,  you the somber feilds,  so quiet and grey,  washed away in the midsummers rain.  you have your defience,  in which you create your allience,  and your trust in me.  shadows shade still,  beat the rain from the tears,  which you pour most everday.  you are nor the soil,  for which you plant me by,  but the everlasting faint smile.    take thy hand,  hold steady still.  breath you last breath and die.

title: ''I'm a Crotchety Witch''
author: jay
text: ''i'm a crotchety witch living all by myself,  i haven't one crony,  not ogre nor elf.  no wizard or warlock drops by for a stay hobgoblins avoid me- i like it that way.   my rooms are suffused with perennial gloom.  i never go out  i've retired my broom.  i don't even bother to boil a few brews,  so i'm not to blame if there's ooze in your shoes.   today is my b-day,  i baked a stale cake,  instead of a candle,  i stuck in a snake,  i've turned 30303,  the snake got away- happy b-day to me!''

title: That Terrible Sneeze
author: jay
text: professor mcpickle was starting to tickle right at the end of his nose,  and so the main issue was finding a tissue which was lurking inside of his clothes.   he knew he would sneeze,  go weak at the knees and make a most terrible racket.  so he searched high and low from his hat to his toe,  for a hanky,  last seen in his jacket.   but all he could find was some old bacon rind,  a clock and a bottle of port.  and all this nose-itching and tweaking and twitching was still a sneeze waiting to snort.   he pulled out a log and a small furry dog and a kite which he'd fly in the breeze.  he found seven crumpets,  a nun and two trumpets,  but still he was going to sneeze.   he searched through his coat,  found four cows and a goat   and fifteen yards of green hose.  so he still could not mop and nor could he stop that big itch at the end of his nose.   swiss cheese and a bike,  and a fellow called mike came tumbling from his left sleeve.  a chicken called leslie and a statue of presley,  but nothing to hinder his sneeze.   here it came now.  he could feel it,  and how.  that tickle had just grew and grew.  these strange things on the table had all been unable to stop him from sneezing:   achoo!  and so the old prof,  with a sneeze (and a cough) had blown off all of his clothes and under all these sat a blue hankerchief with which he now blew his nose.

title: Baby Brother

text: a new baby brother was born today.  an addition to the family,  though born far away.   his first name is timur,  and his last name is fine.  i think it is great because it's the same as mine.   i look down and see those eyes,  a great brown.  never really looking up,  but always down.   he is just a newborn,  so he is really guite squirmy.  i think he reminds me of a little,  tiny wormy.   he is sleeping a lot; most of the day.  and when he is not,  he is feeding away.   timur does not look at all like our dad.  yet,  i don't think,  it makes him mad.   no,  his mom is the one that gave him his style.  and you can tell from almost a mile.   for most,  the births are quite confusing.  i think that they are quite amusing.   timur was born in switzerland.  oh,  what a glorious day.  his mom was born in kazakstan,  and dad in u. s. a.   this has been my poem,  i hope you know about my. . .  oops,  sorry,  gotta go,  i think i hear him cry.

title: A Sea of Darkness
author: jenny
text: when the sun falls from the sky to visit the other side of the world darkness takes over.  a deep blue that is almost black filled with twinkling dots of light you can play connect the dots with the twinkling lights and find or just admire the view.  when you look up where the sun used to be you see a pale,  whitish sphere glimmering softly.  some say that sphere is made out of green cheese and that at certain times it grows smaller and bigger.  when you look at the sea of stars you wonder if it ever ends where does it begin? where does it end? does it even have a beginning? you canâ’t tell because it goes on forever and ever no sign of ever stopping a canyon with a depth that goes on forever making you think humans are microscopic compared to the entire universe.

title: THE ARCTIC WOLF PACK
author: jenny
text: s i sit uncomfortably guarding my flock of reindeer i gaze over the arctic rugged landscape.  tall,  rocky snowy mountains stick up  almost touching the gray clouds above rocky slopes with slushy snow in the crevices making transportation by foot exceedingly difficult and the bitterly cold air,  uggh,  iâ’ll never get used to it.  as i am about to fall asleep,  an awful howling is heard.  i open my eyes and see a large pure white arctic wolf howling its head off.   i reach slowly for my fishing pole,  my sudden movement causing it to bare its teeth.  other wolves,  some gray some brown,  others a dirty white silently kill four reindeer with their lethal fangs and claws i casually began scraping against the snow,  gathering it as soon as the white arctic wolf turns its gaze away from me i gather all the snow in the world and compacted it into a ball in the palm of my hand and threw it at the wolf who then ran away with its pack,  not daring to look back.

title: Roses and Thorns
author: jennyfer
text: i am from morning dew cold against small bare feet and birds chirping a beautiful song i have yet to learn the rhythm of.  from nature that sounds like the most beautiful orchestra i've ever heard,  opening my tired eyes to the world.  from a carpet of dandelions dancing with the wind.  i am from soft green grass and innocent blue eyes yearning to watch the sunrise.  from watching the sun paint the sky in red,  orange,  and yellow streaks.  from squinting as the sun sparkled on a fresh blanket of fluffy,  white snow.  i am from campfire stories and long starry nights from watching the sunset,  and a full moon rise from behind the stars.  from whispering the moon a good night and closing my eyes.  i am from a little seed but now i am a flower.  a spreading rose bush with thorns so sharp though pierce your skin and your heart.

title: A Final Bow
author: jerry
text: sunshine poured through the silent halls on a march day full of bird calls outside,  horses neighed in their stalls far away,  you could hear the waterfalls.   a gentle breeze stroked a person's hairs brushing him with warm airs a crowd is minding his affairs  watching him coming up the stairs.   as he came to the podium,  he cleared his throat minded his cap and dusted his coat chewed a piece of black-eyed oat again,  he coughed and cleared his throat.   he gazed around and said ''my friends,  i have achieved many dreams and met all ends for focusing on my future is what i intends so,  i am retiring,  my friends.    a man cried out ''to have you quitting is more than i can bear why can't you stay and have another great year? you do not have to end your sports career because you are always welcomed everywhere.   ''i had seen you skating like an angel upon the ice rink you soars and puts the basketball in before one could think when you are holding a bat,  no pitcher dare to blink really,  it seems like you are always the strongest link.   ''on the football field,  you amaze me with those spectacular catches i still remember those olympic hockey matches you do not realize how many souvenirs people likes to snatches -your jerseys,  books,  and door-latches.   the person replied'' chris,  i am forty-nine i am no longer tall and fine my hairs are in decline now i do not want to be in any headline.   ''i am retiring to control crime since i am past my prime to stay,  i cannot offer my friends any joy because i am playing sports worse than a limping boy.    ''to retire,  i have no regrets i asked you not to have any frets i want to be remembered,  not be forgotten memories should not decay and become rotten.   ''so i am making a final bow but i am trying to make a sincere vow that i will always be part of this team who helped me accomplish my biggest dream.   then the person coughed and walked out into the open sky the crowd clapped,  grimaced,  but did not cry life,  like leafless winter trees,  will go on but there will always be laughter and fun.

title: YouÂ’re only friend and the sea
author: jes
text: when youâ’re on the sea your only friend is your boat you and your boat have only one enemy but it is deceiving,  rough and no one can control it.  it is the sea.  you watch the bold waveâ’s crash and eat away at the bow.  you smell the summer air and the salt in the in your mouth.  when you see the perfect gust of wind on the water you ready your jibe and main sail.  you get so exhilarated waiting for it.  then it hits you,  you feel like you are flying.  to keep youâ’re self from capsizing you hook yourself to the trapeze and stand on the tank.  you lean so far out your practically vertical.  the wind is so strong that your boat is vertical to.  the other tank is almost under water.  from afar it looks like i am standing.  then you let out your sail and slow down getting ready for your next tach or jibe.  when you sail you can feel the burning fireball of a sun on your back.  the burn on your hands from your sheets and the pull of the tiller is strangely satisfying.  this is what all sailors live for.

title: Summer
author: jessica
text: school is out,  i'm finally free and my parents don't know what to do with me,  i've been looking forward to this all year,  but my tire has gone flat; that hopeful dream ruined,  drat! now i never leave the house; fortunately for my parents i'm quiet like a mouse,  i normally sit in my room reading a book,  a story of a flying boy and a captain named hook,  or i like to take things apart,  but that's not how i got so smart,  i look through the dictionary to learn some new words,  or watch a documentary on weird-looking birds,  another of my hobbies is drawing,  so you seei like drawing insects,  such as the bee,  i make colorful works of art,  things that come straight from the heart,  so i suppose the summer won't be that bad i thought i would end up just being sad,  but like all great things,  such as this poem,  must come to an end,  i'll see you around later; but there is a bike tire i must mend.

title: Holidays
author: jessica
text: it's that certain time of year,  where people tend to get filled with cheer,  in all different shapes they run about,  some very tall others quite stout,  they hurry in stores to buy presents and gifts,  it makes me think their spirits are on lifts,  wrapping and taping and ripping and stuffing,  even i cannot say it's all for nothing,  parents run to get to the sale while children send letters to santa in the mail,  so restless and excited no child finds sleep,  it's useless to try,  they won't even count sheep,  christmas day is soon to come and not one soul is sad or glum,  that special day has come at last,  all worries and sad things are in the past,  people are much too happy to concentrate on such things,  with carrollers singing and bells loud rings,  you see smiles and hear laughter,  but it might not be quite the same the day after,  it's a pity it's not like this all year,  people being kind,  their hearts filled with cheer,  but at least there's that time to look forward to and wait,  this christmas was good,  but let's make the next one great.

title: FROME THE

title: 56 Feet in an Evergreen Tree
author: jessica
text: fifty-six feet in an evergreen tree; that is my goal,  now i start.       the wind's making trouble,       the branches all wobble,  but nothing can frighten my heart.   fifty-six feet in an evergreen tree and counting; now fifty-seven.       i climb very high      and break through to the sky and blink at the bright blue heavens.   fifty-six feet in an evergreen tree.  my feet finally touch the ground.       i want to climb more,       use a tree to help soar,  but recess is over. . .  for now.

title: Fantasy
author: jessica
text: what fantasies can a writer muster? how far from this world can he stretch his mind? what tales of heroes and swordplay and plunder? what will he gain,  and what leave behind?  what will he dream of that no one else knows? he alone holds the key to regions unknown.  how will his character shine and show the story invented by him alone?  now he has thought of the peril and danger.  now carefully choses the words to portray whatever he wishes,  whatever he savors,  whatever can make us wonder and gaze.   victory to he that do that! encouraging us through hidden morals.  making us admire and look longingly at baring courage,  even through the worst smiles!

title: Nellie Bly
author: jessica
text: strength is only found within the faithful nellie bly.  she didn't hesitate to try,  to let things fly.  she put her life in danger,  when she flew around the world.  in seventy days around the world she whirled.  a journal report as motivation,  to help those insane.   she went to an insane asylum,  to break the abusive chain.  there is no need to ask why,  there is hope.  whith the the faithful nellie bly.

title: Nellie Bly
author: jessica
text: the forever faithful nellie bly, had considered the lives of others.  she tried so hard to make hearts fly, in a place where abuse covers.  she traveled the world in seventy days,  that forever faithful nllie bly.  she made an impact in many ways,  this i cannot lie.  she helped the helpless,   in an insane asylum.  she filled the hopes of the hopeless,  and stayed always by them.  she reported the abuses,   through her journal report.  though she had emotional bruises,  i'd have to add she should take it to court.  the forever faithful nellie bly,  really did make hearts fly.

title: Rain
author: jessica marie
text: the rain rolls down the windows in streams,  the sky is clouded the whole world dark it seems.   it's friday night my ''friends'' are out,  leaving me to sit and pout.   the phone rings once,  i pick it up,  putting down my coffee cup.   but it's only for my mom,  i soon find,  how could i be so blind.   i sit back down and watch the rain,  staining  my heart with eternal pain.   being alone,  i slip deeper into depression,  contemplating to myself my true confession.   sooner or later,  though,  i finally fall asleep,  deeper and deeper into a dream i seep.   into a world where anything is at my reach,  i could be shopping,  have true friends,  or be at the beach.   where i' m not by myself and loved by someone,  here in  my dream where i'm not shun

title: The Beach
author: jessica schaefer
text: the beach is a calm and a gentle place where little kids can play each and every day.     the sun is real hot,  the sand is real toasty,  the cold refreshing drinks,  kids play and parents relax,  and no one will ever forget this day.     the birds that fly across the sky,  while the sun is dancing so brightly up high.     when the dogs run across the beach and families picnic out,  but sadly and shortly after,  the day is almost out.    the sky slowly becomes filled up with darkness,  although the sky was still nearly blue,  while the sun hid and the moon almost came out,  it was almost time for the beautiful sunset!    the sunset on the beach ended the great day at the beach!

title: Recipe for an Actress

text: first make the inside faithful and kind; make the next layer fine and divine.  be sure to add confidence and protection from fear.  make her kind,  and her conscience clear.  add bruises and scratches to make her tough.  make her lean,  give her beauty,  give her strength enough.  make her hair silky and straight; be sure to have her sprinkled with faith.  but now comes the hardest part of all; make her feel okay if she has a downfall.  set her heart towards victory,  and brain without fear.  make her smile everyday from ear to ear.  no matter how old or young,  it doesnâ’t matter which,  for it always seems that an actress is meant to fulfill her dreams.

title: My Angel

title: Mother's Day Poem
author: joy
text: flowers bloom in the month of may,  birds chirp cheerfully at dawn,  nests are made and eggs are laid,  as a mother doe greets her fawn.   the season of birth and motherhood,  the beginning of a special love,  as a mother looks down at a curious newborn,  and as the baby sees a loving face above.   now we thank our mothers,  for everything they've done,  caring for us with so much love,  and bringing light into our lives like the sun.   we'd like to say how much,  our mothers truly mean,  giving us the joy of life,  and the quiet nights of dreams.   mother's day is the time,  we smile and try to be good,  because we truly hope that our mothers,  enjoy the experience of motherhood.

title: Springtime Waterfall
author: joy
text: in the mountains and forests so deep,  springtime awakes from long winter sleep.  flowers and greens underneath sprout,  as creatures of all kinds awake and come out.  to enjoy the beautiful nature of spring,  and see the little birds dance and sing.   a waterfall in the distance tinkles and crashes,  as it hits the water and splashes! it comes from above in the mountains and hills,  and over the ledge the water all spills,  down,  down,  for all creatures to see,  oh,  how beautiful spring can really be!

title: An Upwards Fall
author: joye
text: i've been traversing skyward carving a staircase to heaven i guess i didn't feel a worsening breeze because i lost my balance scraped down the silver staircase down a stairway to heaven before i bumped to the bottom step.   a hole is here a dark chasm stretching beyond what i can see,  the stink of smokeless fore rising out.  an ancient timeless wail,  i can hardly hear because the wind rushes by me,  a giant wave,  to bringe off my little ledge amd and toss me down.   no one will find you if you tumble down and no one down here wishes to be found it seems i hang suspended,  dread building,  before i realise the whistling in my ears is airless air being hurried past me.   an eternity after,  i hit the bottom like a kite landing in the sand gracefully,  suddenly,  folding up.   i feel nothing,  see nothing,  taste gritty sand on my tongue.  before my eyes close,  i see something glitter.  is it a star?  i can see the silly sparkling staircase,  so short.  once so important.  but as i smell impending fire i see something greater ahead.   and then,  mind closes,  and i relax.

title: Cinderella and Bella
author: julia
text: many stories have been told of recent tales and of old.  many stories i do know of summer's garden.   winter's snow many stories have been written of little kittens socks and mittens but now i come  here to tell  a story  that is neither recent nor old.  that is neither found in summer's garden or in winter's snow that is not about kittens socks nor mittens.  i come to tell a story about  cinderella (and of course,  little bella).  bella always dressed in yellow.  cindy  though dressed in a blue,  kind of hue.  bella  looked like cinderella and so they decided to  switch places.  (because they had the same faces) however bella did not like  the blue kind of hue that cindy wore.  and cinderella thought that yellow was just such a bore.  and both of them refused to wear the apparel of the other.  so they decided to just be themselves.  like you should always be cause sometimes being yourself  is the best person you can be.

title: Perfect  Day
author: julia
text: it was a perfect day with a little breeze,   with a smile on i went through my day with ease.   it so sunny and warm so i was in my yard because passing up a day like this would be hard.   i looked up and saw the sky was as blue as an ocean,   and i came up with a very good notion.   a day like this was meant to be spent at the pool,  the sun so hot,  but the water so cool.   the pool became crowded,  my friends became bored,  so we looked for the place where volleyballs were stored.   we passed,  we hit,  we set and spiked,  it soon became late so home we biked.   it started getting darker,  it soon became evening,  i became tired and had thoughts of sleeping.   i looked outside and saw the moonlight,  the clouds came in and the rain blurred the sight.   the thunder and lighting kept me awake,  in anger i shouted â“stop for goodness stake!â”  i fell asleep thinking. . .  how can a day that was so gorgeous and bright,  turn into such a horrible night.

title: Wind
author: julie
text: wind begins softly,  like a whisper,  cool against my face while i walk.  it plays,  making the grass flutter,  and letting the wind chimes outside my window  dance their own ballet and sing their silvery,  tinkling song.    then wind grows bigger,  like a shout,  knocking over trash cans,  messing up ladiesâ’ new hairdos on a spring day,  kicking up all the sand on the playground into a cloud that swirls and swirls.   then it turns angry,  like a roar,  breaking trees in half like toothpicks,  twirling houses off their bases,   screaming through the trees so that even in the day light,   the sound scares you.    not all wind is alike.

title: Remembering
author: june
text: remembering you   it's been six years sinse you went away i've thought of you every single day.  i've moved on with my life as you ask me to,  but there will never be another you!    life must go on as the years pass by.  and we don't always understand why.  god only lets us know what he wants us to.  then he says my child,  now it up to you.    it's been said,  you only have one true love,  the one you'll never forget. it's been awhile sinse you went away,  and i'm not over you yet.     i know your happy in heaven.  i can almost see you smile.  i can hear you say in soft spoken words.  you'll be here to in awhile.     you know i'll never forget you,  and you know i'm  not all alone.  i did what you ask me to do.  i picked up my life and moved on.     i felt strong when you were here with me, and nothing stood in our way.  i just wanted you to know that's the best life i've had, and i'll have it again someday.     my dear,  i met a very loving man, and we've started our life anew.  it won't be like the life we once had,  but then,  you wouldn't have wanted it to.     i'm still taking one day at a time,  it seems to be all i can do.  as i sit here writing this poem,  i'm still remembering you!
